      <title outputclass="H4ForH3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.302-5</ph> Authorized
or required by statute.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d384e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="abcRunin"
                outputclass="H5_abcRunin"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                   Authority.</p>
               <ol id="d384e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123FL" outputclass="H6_123FL" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Citations: <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10
U.S.C.2304(c)(5)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41
U.S.C.3304(a)(5)</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e42" rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Full
and open <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.302-5 by revising paragraph (a)(2).?>competition <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>need not be provided for when–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e48" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e56" rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                               A statute
expressly authorizes or requires that the acquisition be made through
another agency or from a specified source; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e65" rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                               The agency’s
need is for a brand name commercial item for authorized resale.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e78" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Application</i>.
This authority may be used when statutes, such as the following,
expressly authorize or require that acquisition be made from a specified
source or through another agency:</p>
               <ol id="d384e83" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e91" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Federal Prison Industries (UNICOR) <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">18
U.S.C. 4124</xref>(see <xref href="FAR-i1117091.dita#i1117091"
                              base="i1117091"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e106" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Qualified nonprofit agencies
for the blind or other severely disabled <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41
U.S.C.chapter 85,</xref> Committee for Purchase From People Who
Are Blind or Severely Disabled (see <xref href="FAR-i1116916.dita#i1116916"
                              base="i1116916"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.7</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e121" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                         Government Printing and Binding <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">44
U.S.C. 501-504</xref>, 1121 (see <xref href="FAR-i1116866.dita#i1116866"
                              base="i1116866"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  8.8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e136" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                         Sole source awards under the
8(a) Program (15 U.S.C. 637), but see <xref href="FAR-i1119735.dita#i1119735"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> for
requirements for justification and approval of sole-source 8(a)
awards over $22 million. (See subpart <xref href="FAR-i1099848.dita#i1099848"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e151" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                         Sole source awards under the
HUBZone Act of 1997-<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15
U.S.C.657a</xref> (see <xref href="FAR-i1099639.dita#i1099639"
                              base="i1099639"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1306</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e167" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                         Sole source awards under the
Veterans Benefits Act of 2003 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15
U.S.C.657f</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="i1119663"
                      otherprops="123"
                      outputclass="H6_123"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e179" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        
                         Sole source
awards under the WOSB Program–<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref "> 15
U.S.C. 637(m)</xref> (see <xref href="FAR-i1099284.dita#i1099284"
                              base="i1099284"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1506</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="abcRunin"
                outputclass="H5_abcRunin"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d391e196" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                   Limitations.</p>
               <ol id="d384e198" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123FL" outputclass="H6_123FL" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e206" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         This authority shall not be used
when a provision of law requires an agency to award a new contract
to a specified non-Federal Government entity unless the provision
of law specifically—</p>
                     <ol id="d384e208" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e216" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                               Identifies
the entity involved;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e225" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                               Refers
to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10
U.S.C.2304(k)</xref> for armed services acquisitions or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41
U.S.C. 3105</xref> for civilian agency acquisitions; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e240" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                               States
that award to that entity shall be made in contravention of the
merit-based selection procedures in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2304(k)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41
U.S.C. 3105</xref>, as appropriate. However, this limitation does
not apply–</p>
                           <ol id="d384e248" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li otherprops="ABC" outputclass="H8_ABC" class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d391e256" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                     When the work provided for in
the contract is a continuation of the work performed by the specified
entity under a preceding contract; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li otherprops="ABC" outputclass="H8_ABC" class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d391e265" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                      To any contract requiring the
National Academy of Sciences to investigate, examine, or experiment
upon any subject of science or art of significance to an executive
agency and to report on those matters to the Congress or any agency
of the Federal Government.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e278" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Contracts awarded using this
authority shall be supported by the written justifications and approvals
described in <xref href="FAR-i1119735.dita#i1119735"
                              base="i1119735"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.303</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                              base="i1119818"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>,
except for–</p>
                     <ol id="d384e286" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e294" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                               Contracts
awarded under (a)(2)(ii) or (b)(2) of this subsection;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e303" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                               Contracts
awarded under (a)(2)(i) of this subsection when the statute expressly
requires that the procurement be made from a specified source. (Justification
and approval requirements apply when the statute authorizes, but does
not require, that the procurement be made from a specified source);
or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d391e312" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                               Contracts
less than or equal to $22 million awarded under (b)(4) of this subsection.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d391e323" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                         The authority in (a)(2)(ii) of
this subsection may be used only for purchases of brand-name commercial
items for resale through commissaries or other similar facilities.
Ordinarily, these purchases will involve articles desired or preferred
by customers of the selling activities (but see <xref href="FAR-i1119438.dita#i1119438"
                              base="i1119438"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">6.301</xref>(d)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
